{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778698694,"nonce":"AOttekE3EQE6nbCttttKSNhb6sI=","message":"**Plotting convention: profile-comparison subplots share y-axes by default** (surfaced from `06f7faf` refinement).\n\nMulti-panel profile-comparison figures (forward-velocity, hold-drift, and per-replicate variants) must share y-axes across panels — otherwise each panel auto-scales independently and hides the cross-condition magnitude differences the layout is meant to expose. This is now enforced at the plot-helper level via `rlrmp.viz.profile_comparison_grid` (default `shared_yaxes='all'`), so analysis scripts don't need to set it per call site. Codified in CLAUDE.md under \"Plotting Conventions\".\n\nAdopting agents working on new analyses with cross-condition profile comparison should route through `profile_comparison_grid`; raw `plotly.subplots.make_subplots` for that figure family will diverge from the convention.","files":null}]}